data.title: Last Of The Lima, Ohio Chain
data.text: This was once part of an attempt to franchise the Lima, Ohio chain.  It is now run by separate owners but retains the name.  The hamburgers use the same style and labeling....their secret is a bit of sugar in the meat before it is cooked.  Hamburgers are good, fries fresh cut.....a decent hamburger joint.

data.title: Classic burger, fry, shake
data.text: If you're craving a burger, fry, and a shake, this is the place. Service is usually pretty . It's also the place where Lansing political types eat lunch.

data.title: Not what it could be.
data.text: Fries are great.  Decor and food not the freshest.  Interior dated.  Wouldn't be a place I would have to go when back in town.

data.title: Olive Burger
data.text:
I have been going to the Kewpee with my Mom and Auntie Gladys (owner) since Kindergarten.  Have always loved the Olive burger and hot fudge sundae!  

Great family owned place.  say Hi! to Russ Weston - works there on Saturdays @ 99 years young.

data.title: What Changed??
data.text: My all time go to for an olive burger.  My son came home from Washington for a visit and we both headed to Kewpie for there famous olive burger.  It was greasy, and we both tasted it for the remainder of the evening, so disappointed.

data.title: My new go to place for a great burger
data.text: This is a hidden gem in downtown Lansing. Unique decor, great hamburgers and turkey burgers. The prices are fair, the service is good, and the olive burger is a taste treat. Easily a top five burger in my estimation.

data.title: Good good at good prices
data.text: We had burgers and onion rings and were very satisfied. Service was nice but slow for a not very busy Good Friday lunch.

data.title: BEST RESTERAUNT IN LANSING
data.text: The food is excellent and so is the staff.. if you are looking for a place to eat  go here!!! they open at 8:00 am and close at 6pm.. thisis an excellent family resteraunt...

data.title: Great food Great atmosphere
data.text: Ate lunch at Kewpee today - first time going on a weekday.  The place was hopping with business people and other assorted visitors but our wait was minimal.  While we waited the dearest elderly gentleman chatted with us.  Later learned it was Russ (owner or owner's father?)  As the waitress took us to an open booth, he told her he had a better one and led us to one with a little more room.  The waitress laughed and said she didn't argue with Russ!  Our group ordered the fish basket with onion rings;  Greek chicken pita and 1/2 order of the OGrady.  The OGrady is a hamburger bun topped by a hamburg patty covered in chili and melted cheese. Everyone was very happy with their food.  Good size portions and all very tasty.  Service was great.  Russ came by a couple of times to check on us too and see what we ordered.  Next time he said we have to get the Oliver Burger!  It's a family atmosphere, nothing fancy, with a pretty varied menu.  Will be going back!

data.title: The place to see & be seen at lunch downtown.
data.text: Love the family vibe. You are treated like you have been coming for years because most guests have!  Here for lunch today, speedy crazy atmosphere with men in suits, students in pajamas, and everything in between.  All here because the food is always good.  Great burgers, I love the turkey reuben with homemade coleslaw on swirl rye with gooey cheese.  Order the sweet potatoes fries with garlic salt, like Tammie our server suggested. Awesome!  Cool local spot, be prepared for tough parking on the street and sandwiches wrapped in wax paper & styrofoam cups-- all part of its charm!

data.title: Great food
data.text:
Kind of hidden away, but well worth looking for. 
Great food and reasonable prices.
If you're in the area, look this place up.

data.title: Established lunch spot with terrible service
data.text:
First time visitor here.  My sister and I went on a Monday during the lunch hour -didn't look too busy.  First off, we couldn't tell who worked there, they all dress in street clothes.  We took awhile deciding what we wanted, and had a lot of questions...could tell our waitress was a bit annoyed.

We ordered the cherry burger to share and two chicken salads, one with cheese and one without (cheese on the side).  The burger came out first while our chicken was cooking, which was fine.  But we couldn't even start eating it because we didn't have silverware.  Took a while for our waitress to come back around, and when we asked her for some she didn't even apologize or anything, just dropped off some she just pulled off another table and had to go around the corner to grab more.  
Salads came to the table and the first one she dropped off she said "this one is without cheese" -she left and we looked at two of the same salads, with cheese.  She came back around and we told her, she was annoyed that the cooks screwed it up, sighed and said she would get another.  We said no don't worry about it, just knock some money off the tab or something.  
Salad was great, chicken was delicious.  Burger was different but good!  Would definitely go back to try more food.  Asked the waitress for a top to the cheese container and she came back and set a styrofoam pop top down and walked away.  We didn't say anything to her and just said forget it.  After we were finished, she picked up our plates and the cheese and it still didn't even occur to her that she brought the wrong top and that we said we wanted to take the cheese.  Slow down lady and think!

data.title: Hidden treasure in downtown Lansing
data.text:
This month I was able to visit Kewpees for the first time and I was pleasantly surprised. A couple of co-workers and I walked here for take out during our lunch break. They were very busy but we were still able to get right up to the counter to order our food. They have a convenient bench to sit on while you wait for take out orders. The wait was minimal. I ordered the chicken Caesar wrap and it was delicious and large portioned, I could only eat half of it in one sitting. I can't wait to go back here and try something else.
Being from Lansing, I think the reason why I had never eaten here before is because of the restaurant's "dark" exterior. Don't let this fool you; inside there are great people and great food. If you are downtown Lansing looking for a non-chain local eatery, this is the spot to go.

data.title: It was hot... but the potato soup was awesome.
data.text: This place is steeped in history especially their olive burgers.  I had potato soup and a hamburger.  The waitstaff was great and my guest and I really enjoyed the fast moving pace and the fact that you could tell that many who were eating there were long time fans.

data.title: Enjoyable experience for our family
data.text: I took my three young children to Impressions 5 Museum, and afterwards we needed some lunch.  We walked about three blocks to Kewpee's.  The kids enjoyed the decor (it's in an old downtown building), and while the food was a little expensive, the kids menu had actual kid favorites on it, including peanut butter and jelly!  I ordered a chicken salad sandwich that was very tasty.

data.title: The Very Best Olive Burger
data.text: This has been a favorite of our families for years.  My Dad & I try to get there about once every 3 months and we always order the same thing the "Olive Burger" can't be beat.  They also make great onion rings and there home made Chicken Tortilla soup is the best as well.

data.title: Best Onion Rings
data.text: We both had a burger i had a side of onion rings and hubby had a side of fries, very very good. We would go back!!

data.title: A nice sandwich shop
data.text: A good sandwich shop in downtown Lansing. A good selection and lunch specials. Staff was friendly and helpful. A little over a block from the State Capital near a number of other eateries.
